        "desc": "Steps from the court below lead up to this terrace upon which the great tower of\nAvallone stands. Unique in construction, the tower is hollow, the halls of the\nlevels being but the outer shell. The base of the tower is in fact raised upon\nfour great stone columns, each some four score paces in circumference.\nTransparent crystalline stairs spiral up each column into halls of the first\nlevel. In the centre of the terrace, there is a silver pool, but it does not\nlook like it contains water.\n",
