        "desc": "Jutting out into the sea, this treeless high-cliffed promontory is the nesting\nplace of uncounted numbers of gulls, petrels and pale cormorants. Many of these\nbirds wheel above or cruise the near sea, diving for silvery fish, and their\nwails and calls fill the ears. Mixed with the sharp smells of the sea or the\nmany subtle fragrances which waft from Avallone.\n",
